[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(48) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "To mount Zalmon.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Evidently the nearest spot where he could get wood for his hideous design. Zalmon means ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shady. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 68:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we find “as white as snow in Zalmon,” but whether the same mountain is referred to we cannot tell. It may be any of the hills near Gerizim.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "An axe.—Literally, the axes—i.e., he took axes for himself and his army.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "An axe.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "the axes",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—i.e., he took axes for himself and his army.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Cut down a bough.—The word for “a bough” is socath, which does not mean “a bundle of logs,” as the LXX. render it. Every one will recall the scene in Macbeth where Malcolm says:—",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Cut down a bough.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The word for “a bough” is ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "socath, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "which does not mean “a bundle of logs,” as the LXX. render it. Every one will recall the scene in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Macbeth ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "where Malcolm says:—",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“Let every soldier hew him down a bough,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And bear’t before him; thereby shall we shadow",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The numbers of our host, and make discovery",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Err in report of us.”—Acts 5, sc. 4.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But Abimelech merely wanted combustible materials.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "What ye have seen me do.—Comp. what Gideon says in Judges 7:17.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "What ye have seen me do.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Comp. what Gideon says in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 7:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jdg 9:48-51",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jdg 9:48-51",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Zalmon — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A place so called from its shadiness. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thebez — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Another town near Shechem; and, as it seems, within its territory. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thither fled all the men and women — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "All that were not slain in the taking of the town. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And gat them up to the top of the tower — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which was flat and plain, after their manner of building. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
