  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Abimelech got him up to Mount Zalmon,.... A mountain near Shechem, and thought to be the same with Salmon in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 68:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " which seems to have had its name from the shade of the trees which grew upon it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he and all the people that were with him; his whole army: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Abimelech took an axe in his hand, and cut down a bough from the trees; which grew upon Mount Zalmon: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and took it, and laid it on his shoulders; and carried it along with him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and said unto the people that were with him, what ye have seen me do, make haste, and do as I have done; take an axe, and every man cut down a bough with all possible haste, and lay it on his shoulder. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and said unto the people that were with him, what ye have seen me do, make haste, and do as I have done; take an axe, and every man cut down a bough with all possible haste, and lay it on his shoulder. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
